cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on the application of deep reinforcement learning in robot manipulation tasks. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a new reward shaping method for deep reinforcement learning. The System and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also a possibility as it deals with system uncertainty in the learning process. Finally, the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category may also be relevant as it involves state representation modeling.
